BD: FYI. This is very interesting, I've never seen the like. The reading aśulkaiḥ is incorrect (but since that's what the editor reads, your text is fine, except that I'd use minimal correction). It's actually aśuklaḥ, and in addition to what looks like an ai mātrā, there's also a curving line below it. I think that these curves above and below the character must have been proofreader's marks, meaning that kla should be inverted to lka. (Please leave my note in your final version.)
--><lb
