BD: This is a bit messy, but some of the mess is the editor's.
2. He is wrong, the correct reading is ekādaśe (with full vowel e), not caikādaśe. The yā, which is above the e, may perhaps go here (as an introduction before the verse), but I think that is unlikely. All interlinear corrections so far have been BELOW, not ABOVE the place where they go. I can't find a good place for yā in the previous line, but I still think that is more likely than that it belongs in this line. Perhaps the intended reading was madhuka-latikayā, i.e. this yā goes with the kā preceding it, and that kā was meant to be ka.
4. IMPORTANT. The verse needs full verse markup as per the input guide.
